      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2793: isPeerAuthorized() performs trust-store checks for memberStatus/deviceStatus before it knows whether the conversation is one-to-one. The previous one-to-one behavior only treated PermissionStatus::BANNED as denial, while non-one-to-one conversations used repository membership/ban state. Applying global trust-store bans to all conversation types may unintentionally reject valid swarm members in group conversations due to unrelated account-level certificate state. Keep trust-store authorization scoped to one-to-one conversations, and use conversation repository state for other modes.\n```suggestion\n    if (auto conv \u003d pimpl_-\u003egetConversation(convId)) {\n        std::lock_guard lk(conv-\u003emtx);\n        if (conv-\u003econversation) {\n            if (conv-\u003econversation-\u003emode() \u003d\u003d ConversationMode::ONE_TO_ONE) {\n                return memberStatus !\u003d dhtnet::tls::TrustStore::PermissionStatus::BANNED\n                    \u0026\u0026 deviceStatus !\u003d dhtnet::tls::TrustStore::PermissionStatus::BANNED;\n            }\n            return conv-\u003econversation-\u003eisPeerAuthorized(uri, deviceId, includeInvited);\n        }\n```\n",
