      "message": "[Critical] Line 2447: The swarm socket path now only checks whether the device id is banned, but no longer verifies that the remote device belongs to an authorized conversation member. This preserves the original device-ban check but does not apply the new hardened authorization model used for git/conversation channels, so a non-member device that is not explicitly banned can still get a swarm connection attempt. Resolve the peer certificate on the established socket and call isPeerAuthorized(), or add an authorization check in the completion path before returning the socket.\n```suggestion\n// After receiving the socket, validate the authenticated peer before invoking cb.\nauto remoteCert \u003d socket-\u003epeerCertificate();\nif (!remoteCert || !remoteCert-\u003eissuer\n    || !cm-\u003eisPeerAuthorized(convId,\n                             remoteCert-\u003eissuer-\u003egetId().toString(),\n                             socket-\u003edeviceId().toString(),\n                             true)) {\n    socket-\u003eshutdown();\n    cb({});\n    return;\n}\n```\n",
